SIMPLE: higgle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Higgle
<hw>Hig"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Higgled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Higgling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Haggle</er>, or <er>Huckster</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To hawk
or peddle provisions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To chaffer; to stickle for small advantages in
buying and selling; to haggle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A person accustomed to <qex>higgle</qex> about taps.</q>
<rj><qau>Jeffry.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To truck and <qex>higgle</qex> for a private good.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Higgledy-piggledy</ent>⟦br⟧
